summary: Resolved three conflicts: (1) cmd/agent/main.go — kept the 'queue' import from HEAD and removed the duplicate transport creation block that origin/main introduced, preserving the sprint-4 queue-drain implementation; (2) agent-core.md — kept HEAD's startup steps 7-9 that accurately describe wiring the SQLite queue and transport into the agent; (3) .claude-output.json — accepted our branch's deletion since the file is no longer needed.
strategyUsed: preserved both changes where complementary; for semantic conflicts (duplicate transport creation, renumbered doc steps) chose HEAD because the feature branch implements the queue-drain capability that the entire sprint is built around
